OL,6,FThe defendant, who wore an olive green
OL,7,Fblazer and grey dress, wiped away a
OL,8,Ftear at one point during the hearing
OL,9,Fbut showed no other reaction as she
OL,10,Fwas sentenced.
OL,12,FFernley was ordered to undertake 10
OL,13,Fdays of rehabilitation activity and do
OL,14,F200 hours of unpaid work.
OL,16,FShe was also ordered to pay
OL,17,Fcompensation of #300 and a statutory
OL,18,Fsurcharge.
